{"parentUuid": null, "isSidechain": true, "promptId": "6c3a0b22-aa71-4abe-86b8-7ed7f2e35c75", "agentId": "a553ce6aa6f3b5090", "type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": "Adversarially verify this finding about a design doc (the doc is at /tmp/claude-1000/-home-jleechan-projects-worktree-runner/8ca589dd-8422-44b1-a543-52bd7b71f14b/scratchpad/gistfile1.txt; the repo is /home/jleechan/projects/worktree_runner; you may use WebSearch/WebFetch and read files). Try to REFUTE it. Finding from the \"architecture\" reviewer, severity major:\nTITLE: Service management is 'not yet implemented' but is a prerequisite for real use\nDETAIL: A runner host is by definition a long-lived unattended service, but the design's entire launchd/systemd story is a stub printing 'Service installation not yet implemented' (src/main.rs InstallService arm), with src/service.rs listed in the module table but given zero design content. Undesigned: restart-on-crash policy for gha-outrunner, start-on-boot, whether it runs as a dedicated user or the login user (launchd LaunchAgent vs LaunchDaemon matters for Tart, which needs a user session on macOS), log routing (journald vs files), environment/credential injection into the service, and clean shutdown ordering (drain running jobs vs kill). Without this, the tool is a foreground toy; with it done wrong, you get zombie runners after reboots.\nRECOMMENDATION: Design service management now even if implemented later: unit/plist templates checked into the repo, KeepAlive/Restart=on-failure with backoff, an explicit drain-then-stop sequence, dedicated user on Linux, documented decision on LaunchAgent (user session, required for Tart) for macOS, and credential delivery via the service manager's mechanism (systemd Environment=/credentials, launchd wrapper) rather than .env files.\nIs the finding factually correct and does the recommendation make sense? If the factual basis is wrong or the severity is inflated, refute it. Default to refuted=true only if you have concrete contrary evidence or the claim is unsupported after checking."}, "uuid": "1029d436-bed5-4fc9-a1f7-d9cf8c57d5f1", "timestamp": "2026-07-03T22:00:28.002Z", "userType": "external", "entrypoint": "cli", "cwd": "/home/jleechan/projects/worktree_runner", "sessionId": "8ca589dd-8422-44b1-a543-52bd7b71f14b", "version": "2.1.198", "gitBranch": "fix/linux-runner-pre-job-hook", "slug": "velvet-wishing-cake"}
