{"parentUuid": "61b43a9b-4a2c-41a9-afae-689d04f04851", "isSidechain": true, "agentId": "a553ce6aa6f3b5090", "message": {"model": "claude-fable-5", "id": "msg_012qDcFyveSr4t6XDCbcKbz1", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "tool_use", "id": "toolu_015xzukTHjmiCE68XkE9eYBy", "name": "Read", "input": {"file_path": "/tmp/claude-1000/-home-jleechan-projects-worktree-runner/8ca589dd-8422-44b1-a543-52bd7b71f14b/scratchpad/gistfile1.txt"}, "caller": {"type": "direct"}}], "stop_reason": "tool_use", "stop_sequence": null, "stop_details": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 793, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 24200, "cache_read_input_tokens": 33489, "output_tokens": 156, "server_tool_use": {"web_search_requests": 0, "web_fetch_requests": 0}, "service_tier": "standard", "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0, "ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 24200}, "inference_geo": "not_available", "iterations": [{"input_tokens": 793, "output_tokens": 156, "cache_read_input_tokens": 33489, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 24200, "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 24200, "ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0}, "type": "message"}], "speed": "standard"}, "diagnostics": null}, "requestId": "req_011CcfsnZtMWqCCzfZmoP8Nw", "attributionAgent": "workflow-subagent", "type": "assistant", "uuid": "73022684-a837-4bd4-acdd-3b60a3ecff37", "timestamp": "2026-07-03T22:00:42.127Z", "userType": "external", "entrypoint": "cli", "cwd": "/home/jleechan/projects/worktree_runner", "sessionId": "8ca589dd-8422-44b1-a543-52bd7b71f14b", "version": "2.1.198", "gitBranch": "fix/linux-runner-pre-job-hook", "slug": "velvet-wishing-cake"}
{"parentUuid": "73022684-a837-4bd4-acdd-3b60a3ecff37", "isSidechain": true, "promptId": "6c3a0b22-aa71-4abe-86b8-7ed7f2e35c75", "agentId": "a553ce6aa6f3b5090", "type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "toolu_015xzukTHjmiCE68XkE9eYBy", "type": "tool_result", "content": "1\t\u2705 Full Self-Contained Design + Skeleton Code\n2\tHere is a complete, standalone design and Rust skeleton for gha-isolated \u2014 a wrapper CLI around gha-outrunner that gives you unified, reliable, VM-preferring GitHub Actions runners across macOS, Linux, and GCE.\n3\t\n4\t1. Project Overview\n5\tTool Name: gha-isolated\n6\tPurpose: Provide a single, easy-to-use CLI that runs self-hosted GitHub Actions runners with the strongest practical isolation available on the current platform, while keeping operational overhead low.\n7\tCore Principles\n8\t\t\u2022\tPrefer VM-level isolation when possible (Tart on macOS, libvirt on Linux).\n9\t\t\u2022\tFall back gracefully to container isolation with hard resource limits.\n10\t\t\u2022\tUse GitHub Scale Sets + ephemeral runners by default.\n11\t\t\u2022\tApply consistent resource protection everywhere.\n12\t\t\u2022\tWork the same way on a developer laptop and inside a GCE VM.\n13\tSupported Platforms (v1 target)\n14\t\t\u2022\tmacOS (Apple Silicon) \u2192 Tart backend (VMs)\n15\t\t\u2022\tLinux with KVM \u2192 libvirt backend (VMs)\n16\t\t\u2022\tLinux / GCE (no strong KVM) \u2192 Docker + Sysbox (with strict limits)\n17\t\t\u2022\tGCE \u2192 Same as Linux (run inside a GCE VM)\n18\t\n19\t2. High-Level Architecture\n20\tgha-isolated (Rust binary)\n21\t\u251c\u2500\u2500 CLI (clap)\n22\t\u251c\u2500\u2500 Platform Detection\n23\t\u251c\u2500\u2500 Backend Selection (Tart / libvirt / Docker+Sysbox)\n24\t\u251c\u2500\u2500 Config Generation (outrunner.yml + resource limits)\n25\t\u251c\u2500\u2500 Runner Lifecycle (start/stop/status via gha-outrunner)\n26\t\u251c\u2500\u2500 Service Management (systemd / launchd)\n27\t\u2514\u2500\u2500 Optional GCE helpers\n28\tData Flow (start command)\n29\t\t1\tDetect platform + capabilities\n30\t\t2\tChoose best backend\n31\t\t3\tGenerate/validate outrunner.yml with resource limits\n32\t\t4\tEnsure prerequisites (gha-outrunner binary, Sysbox/Tart, etc.)\n33\t\t5\tStart gha-outrunner with correct flags/backend\n34\t\n35\t3. Backend Selection Logic\n36\tPlatform\n37\tKVM/Tart?\n38\tChosen Backend\n39\tIsolation\n40\tResource Limits\n41\tmacOS Apple Silicon\n42\tTart available\n43\tTart\n44\tVM\n45\tPer-VM\n46\tLinux + /dev/kvm\n47\tYes\n48\tlibvirt\n49\tVM\n50\tPer-VM\n51\tLinux / GCE\n52\tNo / weak\n53\tdocker + Sysbox\n54\tContainer\n55\tDocker limits\n56\tFallback\n57\t\u2014\n58\tdocker\n59\tContainer\n60\tDocker limits\n61\t\n62\t4. Module Structure\n63\tFile\n64\tResponsibility\n65\tsrc/main.rs\n66\tCLI entrypoint + command routing\n67\tsrc/platform.rs\n68\tOS/arch detection + capability checks\n69\tsrc/backend.rs\n70\tBackend selection + validation\n71\tsrc/config.rs\n72\tGenerate outrunner.yml + resource limits\n73\tsrc/runner.rs\n74\tStart/stop/status of gha-outrunner\n75\tsrc/service.rs\n76\tInstall as systemd/launchd service\n77\tsrc/limits.rs\n78\tResource limit helpers\n79\t\n80\t5. Skeleton Code (Self-Contained)\n81\t`Cargo.toml`\n82\t[package]\n83\tname = \"gha-isolated\"\n84\tversion = \"0.1.0\"\n85\tedition = \"2021\"\n86\tdescription = \"Unified isolated GitHub Actions runners (VM preferred)\"\n87\t\n88\t[dependencies]\n89\tclap = { version = \"4.5\", features = [\"derive\"] }\n90\tserde = { version = \"1.0\", features = [\"derive\"] }\n91\tserde_yaml = \"0.9\"\n92\twhich = \"6.0\"\n93\tsysinfo = \"0.30\"\n94\tduct = \"0.13\"\n95\tcolored = \"2\"\n96\tanyhow = \"1.0\"\n97\t`src/main.rs`\n98\tuse clap::{Parser, Subcommand};\n99\tuse anyhow::Result;\n100\t\n101\tmod platform;\n102\tmod backend;\n103\tmod config;\n104\tmod runner;\n105\t\n106\t#[derive(Parser)]\n107\t#[command(name = \"gha-isolated\", about = \"Isolated GitHub Actions runners with VM preference\")]\n108\tstruct Cli {\n109\t    #[command(subcommand)]\n110\t    command: Commands,\n111\t}\n112\t\n113\t#[derive(Subcommand)]\n114\tenum Commands {\n115\t    /// Initialize configuration for this machine\n116\t    Init,\n117\t    /// Start the runner(s)\n118\t    Start,\n119\t    /// Stop the runner(s)\n120\t    Stop,\n121\t    /// Show current status\n122\t    Status,\n123\t    /// Install as a persistent system service\n124\t    InstallService,\n125\t}\n126\t\n127\tfn main() -> Result<()> {\n128\t    let cli = Cli::parse();\n129\t\n130\t    match cli.command {\n131\t        Commands::Init => {\n132\t            println!(\"Initializing gha-isolated...\");\n133\t            let plat = platform::detect();\n134\t            let back = backend::select(&plat);\n135\t            println!(\"Detected: {} | Best backend: {:?}\", plat.os, back);\n136\t            config::generate(&plat, &back)?;\n137\t        }\n138\t        Commands::Start => {\n139\t            runner::start()?;\n140\t        }\n141\t        Commands::Stop => {\n142\t            runner::stop()?;\n143\t        }\n144\t        Commands::Status => {\n145\t            runner::status()?;\n146\t        }\n147\t        Commands::InstallService => {\n148\t            println!(\"Service installation not yet implemented\");\n149\t        }\n150\t    }\n151\t\n152\t    Ok(())\n153\t}\n154\t`src/platform.rs`\n155\tuse sysinfo::System;\n156\t\n157\t#[derive(Debug, Clone)]\n158\tpub struct Platform {\n159\t    pub os: String,\n160\t    pub arch: String,\n161\t    pub has_kvm: bool,\n162\t    pub has_tart: bool,\n163\t}\n164\t\n165\tpub fn detect() -> Platform {\n166\t    let mut sys = System::new_all();\n167\t    sys.refresh_all();\n168\t\n169\t    let os = if cfg!(target_os = \"macos\") {\n170\t        \"macos\".to_string()\n171\t    } else if cfg!(target_os = \"linux\") {\n172\t        \"linux\".to_string()\n173\t    } else {\n174\t        \"unknown\".to_string()\n175\t    };\n176\t\n177\t    let arch = std::env::consts::ARCH.to_string();\n178\t\n179\t    let has_kvm = std::path::Path::new(\"/dev/kvm\").exists();\n180\t    let has_tart = which::which(\"tart\").is_ok();\n181\t\n182\t    Platform { os, arch, has_kvm, has_tart }\n183\t}\n184\t`src/backend.rs`\n185\tuse crate::platform::Platform;\n186\t\n187\t#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq)]\n188\tpub enum Backend {\n189\t    Tart,\n190\t    Libvirt,\n191\t    DockerSysbox,\n192\t    Docker,\n193\t}\n194\t\n195\tpub fn select(plat: &Platform) -> Backend {\n196\t    if plat.os == \"macos\" && plat.has_tart {\n197\t        return Backend::Tart;\n198\t    }\n199\t    if plat.os == \"linux\" && plat.has_kvm {\n200\t        return Backend::Libvirt;\n201\t    }\n202\t    if plat.os == \"linux\" {\n203\t        return Backend::DockerSysbox; // assume Sysbox is installed or will be\n204\t    }\n205\t    Backend::Docker\n206\t}\n207\t`src/config.rs`\n208\tuse crate::platform::Platform;\n209\tuse crate::backend::Backend;\n210\tuse anyhow::Result;\n211\t\n212\tpub fn generate(plat: &Platform, backend: &Backend) -> Result<()> {\n213\t    let config = match backend {\n214\t        Backend::Tart | Backend::Libvirt => {\n215\t            // VM backends get per-VM resource limits\n216\t            format!(\n217\t                r#\"\n218\trunners:\n219\t  default:\n220\t    backend: {}\n221\t    labels: [self-hosted, {}]\n222\t    count: 2\n223\t    resources:\n224\t      memory: 4G\n225\t      cpus: 2\n226\t\"#,\n227\t                if *backend == Backend::Tart { \"tart\" } else { \"libvirt\" },\n228\t                plat.os\n229\t            )\n230\t        }\n231\t        _ => {\n232\t            // Docker path with resource limits\n233\t            r#\"\n234\trunners:\n235\t  default:\n236\t    backend: docker\n237\t    labels: [self-hosted, docker]\n238\t    count: 2\n239\t    docker:\n240\t      memory: 4g\n241\t      cpus: 2\n242\t      pids_limit: 100\n243\t\"#\n244\t            .to_string()\n245\t        }\n246\t    };\n247\t\n248\t    std::fs::write(\"outrunner.yml\", config)?;\n249\t    println!(\"Generated outrunner.yml\");\n250\t    Ok(())\n251\t}\n252\t`src/runner.rs` (Skeleton)\n253\tuse duct::cmd;\n254\tuse anyhow::Result;\n255\t\n256\tpub fn start() -> Result<()> {\n257\t    println!(\"Starting gha-outrunner (placeholder)...\");\n258\t    // Example: cmd!(\"gha-outrunner\", \"--config\", \"outrunner.yml\").run()?;\n259\t    Ok(())\n260\t}\n261\t\n262\tpub fn stop() -> Result<()> {\n263\t    println!(\"Stopping runners...\");\n264\t    Ok(())\n265\t}\n266\t\n267\tpub fn status() -> Result<()> {\n268\t    println!(\"Status: Not yet implemented\");\n269\t    Ok(())\n270\t}\n271\t\n272\t6. How to Use (Planned Flow)\n273\t# First time\n274\tgha-isolated init\n275\t\n276\t# Start runners\n277\tgha-isolated start\n278\t\n279\t# Check status\n280\tgha-isolated status\n281\t\n282\t# Install as service (future)\n283\tgha-isolated install-service\n284\tOn GCE: Create a Linux VM \u2192 cargo install gha-isolated (or copy binary) \u2192 run the same commands.\n285\t\n286\tNext Steps\n287\tThis skeleton is runnable today. Would you like me to expand any of these next?\n288\t\t1\tFull runner.rs implementation (actually calling gha-outrunner)\n289\t\t2\tService installation (systemd + launchd)\n290\t\t3\tBetter config model (proper structs + serialization)\n291\t\t4\tPrerequisite installation logic (install Sysbox/Tart automatically where possible)\n292\tJust say which part to flesh out first (or \u201call of them in order\u201d), and I\u2019ll continue building it out.\n293\t"}]}, "uuid": "a45aa678-0368-42c5-97d6-fc038071f679", "timestamp": "2026-07-03T22:00:42.168Z", "sourceToolAssistantUUID": "73022684-a837-4bd4-acdd-3b60a3ecff37", "userType": "external", "entrypoint": "cli", "cwd": "/home/jleechan/projects/worktree_runner", "sessionId": "8ca589dd-8422-44b1-a543-52bd7b71f14b", "version": "2.1.198", "gitBranch": "fix/linux-runner-pre-job-hook", "slug": "velvet-wishing-cake"}
